SIMPLE: thew
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thew
<hw>Thew</hw> <pr>(th⟦umac⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <note>[Chiefly used in
the plural <er>Thews</er> <pr>(th⟦umac⟧z)</pr>.]</note> <ety>[OE.
<ets>thew</ets>, <ets>⟦thorn⟧eau</ets>, manner, habit, strength, AS.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧e⟦aacute⟧w</ets> manner, habit (cf.
<ets>⟦thorn⟧⟦ymac⟧wan</ets> to drive); akin to OS. <ets>thau</ets>
custom, habit, OHG. <ets>dou</ets>. ⟦root⟧56.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Manner; custom; habit; form of behavior; qualities of mind;
disposition; specifically, good qualities; virtues.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>For her great light⟦br⟧
Of sapience, and for her <qex>thews</qex> clear.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Evil speeches destroy good <qex>thews</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Wyclif
(1 Cor. xv. 33).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To be upbrought in gentle <qex>thews</qex> and martial might.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Muscle or strength; nerve; brawn; sinew.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>And I myself, who sat apart⟦br⟧
And watched them, waxed in every limb;⟦br⟧
I felt the <qex>thews</qex> of Anakim,⟦br⟧
The pules of a Titan's heart.</q> <rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thewed</ent>⟦br⟧
